<section class="page-header">
  <h1>Global Infrastructure Map</h1>
  <p>A unified, intelligent view of the world’s infrastructure — the foundation of a global operating system.</p>
</section>

<section class="content">

  <h2>The Vision</h2>
  <p>
    The Global Infrastructure Map is the centerpiece of this platform — a future interactive system that brings together
    infrastructure projects, risks, performance data, and engineering insights from around the world. It is designed to
    evolve into a global operating system for infrastructure planning, delivery, and oversight.
  </p>

  <h2>How the System Works</h2>
  <p>This platform is built on a layered architecture that grows over time:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>1. Map Layer:</strong> A global view of infrastructure projects across sectors and regions.</li>
    <li><strong>2. Data Layer:</strong> Procurement, PMO, risk, oversight, and M&E data feeding each project.</li>
    <li><strong>3. Intelligence Layer:</strong> AI‑powered risk scoring, trend detection, and predictive analytics.</li>
    <li><strong>4. Integration Layer:</strong> Future connections to engineering tools (ANSYS, Autodesk, ESRI, Siemens).</li>
    <li><strong>5. Collaboration Layer:</strong> Contractors, PMOs, donors, and governments sharing insights.</li>
    <li><strong>6. Future Layer:</strong> Expansion into aerospace and off‑planet infrastructure systems.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What the Map Will Show</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Active and planned infrastructure projects worldwide</li>
    <li>Sector layers: roads, energy, water, public facilities, telecom, and more</li>
    <li>Project status, risks, and performance indicators</li>
    <li>Contractor and PMO participation</li>
    <li>Donor and government involvement</li>
    <li>Global trends and emerging infrastructure needs</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Roadmap</h2>
  <p>The Global Infrastructure Map will evolve in phases:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Phase 1 – Vision:</strong> Establish the concept and platform foundation.</li>
    <li><strong>Phase 2 – Prototype:</strong> Build a functional map with sample data and project layers.</li>
    <li><strong>Phase 3 – Integration:</strong> Connect PMO, procurement, risk, and oversight systems.</li>
    <li><strong>Phase 4 – Intelligence:</strong> Add AI‑powered analytics and predictive insights.</li>
    <li><strong>Phase 5 – Global Network:</strong> Enable contractors, PMOs, and donors to collaborate.</li>
    <li><strong>Phase 6 – Frontier Expansion:</strong> Support aerospace and off‑planet infrastructure.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Future Integrations</h2>
  <p>
    As the platform grows, the map will integrate with engineering and simulation ecosystems such as:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>ANSYS – structural and systems simulation</li>
    <li>Autodesk & Bentley – BIM and civil design</li>
    <li>ESRI – GIS and geospatial intelligence</li>
    <li>Siemens – industrial and energy systems</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Global Impact</h2>
  <p>
    The Global Infrastructure Map will help governments, donors, contractors, and PMOs make better decisions, reduce
    risks, improve transparency, and accelerate development across the world.
  </p>

  <h2>Join the Vision</h2>
  <p>
    Contractors, PMOs, donors, and engineering partners will be able to join the platform as it evolves — contributing
    insights, sharing data, and helping build the world’s first global infrastructure operating system.
  </p>

</section>

